MergeSort(wordPairs, 0, wordPairs.Count - 1);
```

Here, we used the Merge Sort algorithm, which is a stable and efficient solution for handling large datasets, as it has a worst-case time complexity of O(n log n). By following these steps, you can sort the words in Column A and B without losing the association between the elements.

